An 18-year-old student, Pekka-Eric Auvinen, went on a shooting rampage at Jokela High School in Tuusula, Finland.
He posted a video on YouTube before the massacre, expressing admiration for past school shooters.
Auvinen shot and killed eight people, including classmates and the headmistress, before taking his own life.
This tragic event shocked the nation, as Finland had never experienced a school shooting of this magnitude before.
The government expressed condolences and ordered flags to be flown at half-mast in honor of the victims.
Auvinen's actions left a community in mourning and raised concerns about gun ownership
